17_18	0.0	The number grows almost daily.
17_19	0.0	At the moment, however, the most watched developments are in Australia, which recently permitted its states and territories to individually license and regulate sports and racetrack betting on the Internet.
17_20	0.0	U.S. gamblers are beginning to discover these legal bookies Down Under who gladly accept wagers from anywhere in the world _ seemingly daring legal retaliation from Uncle Sam.
17_21	0.0	In fact, sports book American Wagering Inc.
17_22	0.0	of Nevada holds one of the Australian licenses.
17_23	0.0	American is the only online Australian operator not accepting U.S. bets, but only because that action could jeopardize its U.S. licenses.
17_24	0.0	That doesn't bother American's CEO, Vic Salerno, who said he was convinced that his company had taken the Internet plunge in the right nation and at the right time.
